feeling: the domestic comfort of working in a warm room after a warm shower
tiredness when the gloomy, indifferent weather seems to reflect your somewhat worn out spirit
the nagging wondering that if you hadn't texted first, that they would have never texted you

the creeping, quiet suspicion that a person you feel a deep romantic connection with may not feel the same way about you; the constant monitoring for a text message that doesn't come; the disappointment when a notification from someone else pops up instead
the dull consciousness of being awake, unable to sleep yet physically tired, sickness pervading the lungs and breath
the quiet excitement of starting a new project that you plan to engage with every day over a long period of time
